<HEADLINE>
NCCU BUILDING TAIWAN'S ONLY CORPUS OF SPOKEN CHINESE
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May 28 (CNA) 05/28/07  17:30:26 (By Y.F. Low)
</P>
<P>
National Chengchi University (NCCU) is building a corpus of
spoken Chinese, the only one of its kind in Taiwan, NCCU
President Wu Se-hwa said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the NCCU Corpus of Spoken Chinese, which
covers materials for the study of Mandarin, Hakka and Minnan, is
part of NCCU's efforts to become a top international university.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, under a platform aimed at facilitating cross-cultural
research, NCCU has set up the Center for the Study of Islamic
Civilization and Thoughts, the first of its kind in the country,
Wu noted,  adding that the university also held an international
conference on "Islam and Modernity" in December last year.
</P>
<P>
Also included in the platform are the Translation Center, the
Center for Cross- Cultural Studies and the Center for European
Cultural Studies, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
On the study abroad program promoted by the university, Wu said
NCCU sent 153 students to 63 foreign universities in 24 countries
for exchanges in 2006.
</P>
<P>
This year, the number of universities and students taking part in
the program will increase by 13 and 29, respectively, Wu said.
</P>
